abstract: >-
  NexusRAG is a fully local retrieval-augmented generation system for
  scientific papers. It combines dense (MiniLM) and sparse (BM25)
  retrieval with reciprocal-rank fusion and cross-encoder reranking,
  verifies each generated sentence against its sources with a
  natural-language-inference model, and re-retrieves when grounding is
  weak. It ships with a reproducible benchmark reporting nDCG@10,
  Recall@20, and sentence-level faithfulness on SciFact and NFCorpus.
